entry.title: customization: Refresh Key Display and DomKey before sending event
entry.content:
For the purposes of Shortcut and Peripheral customization, the VKEY that

is stored by the system will be the VKEY remapped as though it was in

the US english keyboard layout.



Adds four additional accelerators that get remapped based on location.

This includes:

* Semicolon

* Apostrophe

* Backtick

* International Backslash (key to the left of Z on ISO layouts)



These keys will only get remapped based on location if the original VKEY

is not an alphanumeric VKEY. This prevents situations where the VKEY

semantic meaning will be clobbered due to the positional remapping.



Since the keys will only be positionally remapped sometimes, the

shortcuts app must hide cases of shortcuts which are not possible to be

produced in the current layout. This can only happen if the key in the

current layout will NOT be positionally remapped, but in the US layout

it would be remapped.



Bug: b/241965717

entry.title: media/gpu/v4l2: Allow V4L2DevicePoller blocking behaviour
entry.content:
V4L2DevicePoller has two problem re. threading:

- One is that it calls Stop() on an internal thread [1], which

violates AssertBaseSyncPrimitivesAllowed()[2] (because Stop() is

blocking).

- Another is that the member thread uses Wait() [3] and Poll() [4]

(both of which are blocking) on that internal Thread that is constructed as non blockable (and this can't be tweaked BTW).



Fixing V4L2DevicePoller would be risky and complicated, and it's

anyway going to be deprecated (I estimate in the next 6 months or

so). This CL explicitly allows for the blocking behaviour.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:media/gpu/v4l2/v4l2_device_poller.cc;l=85;drc=d70f89acd09b75f61ae0d18689737246eca6c499

[2] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:base/threading/thread_restrictions.cc;l=160-170;drc=9a4c11173d5209a3b813c746e342155896738eb3

[3] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:media/gpu/v4l2/v4l2_device_poller.cc;l=120;drc=d70f89acd09b75f61ae0d18689737246eca6c499

entry.title: Consolidate the observer interface of the allocation/free event dispatcher
entry.content:
This CL bundles all the single parameters of the observer interface

into allocation/free specific dedicated structures. Previously,

extending the observer interface involved quite a lot of different

locations.



With this CL, only those structures need to be extended.



To allow for a clean structure of projects and to avoid dependencies

into PartitionAllocator in case PA is disabled, the Dispatcher

introduces own structures and enums. Analysis of the generated

assembly code shows that these intermediate structures are omitted

by the compiler if the callee can be inlined, which is the case

with the current quick bail out functions of all observers.



Hence, performance is not negatively impacted by these changes.

entry.title: Blink: Make ContextLifecycleNotifier non-virtual
entry.content:
There is no reason for the ContextLifecycleNotifier methods to be

virtual, especially since they do not need to be overridden.



The motivation for this was: in the construction path (i.e., in the

initialization list or inside the constructor) of a

ContextLifecycleNotifier, there was interest in passing `this` into a

HeapMojoRemote, which would rely on calling virtual methods on the CLN,

"during" its construction.



This is bad, so after looking at the virtual methods on

ContextLifecycleNotifier and realizing that they are never overridden,

it seemed simplest to just make them *not* virtual at all.

entry.title: [A11y] Update inherited cached value changes in all descendants
entry.content:
Some cached values in AXObject are dependent on the parent value.

Therefore, when the parent value changes, the values of descendants

must also be updated. Not doing this leads to stale values, which

in turn triggers checks that enforce a clean tree after an

update, and checks that require that children are not invalidated

at an illegal time.



The general fix is that when a value changes that might be inherited,

to set a flag that indicates children need to be updated. This

recursively causes all descendants to be updated during

UpdateTreeIfNeeded().



Specifics:

1. When cached values that are inherited by descendants change, call a

common method, OnInheritedCachedValuesChanged().

2. OnInheritedCachedValuesChanged() differentiates between two cases:

A) Values are changing during a tree update, when a top to bottom sweep of the tree is occurring. In this case, flags are set to ensure the loop

propagates changes to the children of the current node. This will

recursively propagate as long as a descendant changes any inheritable

value.

B) Update occurs outside of UpdateTreeIfNeeded(). In this case, flags

are set so that the next UpdateTreeIfNeeded() will update the descendants of this node.



In both cases, a new flag called child_cached_values_need_update_ is

set to true on the current node. This ensures that when children are

added to a node, that the children all update their cached values.



Fixed: 1506895

manually increasing or off-loading spacing to other suggestions,

- ensures that HeaderView works correctly with all suggestion types,

including carousel.

- 40dp tall,

- 24dp start padding.

entry.title: [omnibox][ml] Cull per ML ranking instead of traditional ranking
entry.content:
go/autocomplete-controller-refactor has some details on the refactor

plan.



This is part 7 of the refactor.



Before this CL, autocomplete passes with transferred matches looked

like:



1. Sort, dedupe, cull, etc the new matches

2. Append the old matches to the new matches

3. ML score the merged matches

4. Sort, dedupe, cull, etc the merged matches



This was problematic, because step 1 would cull matches based on

traditional scores instead of the ML scores. So it could lead to culling

a match that's scored higher by the ML model than another match that

wasn't culled.



This didn't affect the autocomplete passes without transferred matches,

since those only do steps 3 & 4.



This CL moves ML scoring (step 3) before the initial culling (step 1):



3. ML score the new matches

2. Sort, dedupe, cull, etc the new matches

3. Append the old matches to the new matches

4. Sort, dedupe, cull, etc the merged matches



This also helps avoid overwriting the score demotions

`TransferOldMatches()` does.



This is not feature guarded, because the impact on ranking is probably

small.

entry.title: Handle double-error edge case in sql::Database::Open()
entry.content:
Currently, Database::Open() incorrectly returns true when both attempts

at opening the database fail. We're chalking this behavior up to a

simple oversight in Database::OpenInternal()'s error handling. See the

linked crbug for more details.



This CL addresses the root cause by unifying Database::Open()'s error

handling and retry logic. In doing so, it resolves a preexisting TODO.

As a side effect, Database::Open() no longer invokes the error callback

6 times in the double-error scenario, which was why I originally filed

the crbug.

entry.title: Prune more legacy IPC code from RenderFrame, ChildThread, RenderThread
entry.content:
- Do not build RenderFrame as an IPC::Sender/Listener

- Remove public FromRoutingID lookup

- Remove requesting the routing ID from RenderFrame

- Do not build ChildThread as an IPC::Sender

- This leaves all the legacy IPC code in ChildThreadImpl the same.

- We still require legacy IPC for some associated channel interfaces (see

RenderThread::GetChannel callsites, and

RenderThreadObserver::RegisterMojoInterfaces).

- The scheduling differences between associated channel interfaces and

normal associated interfaces still also need to be resolved to disable legacy IPC over the wire.
